Interface ShapeInsetsFunction

All Superinterfaces:

Functional Interface:
This is a functional interface and can therefore be used as the assignment target for a lambda expression or method reference.
@FunctionalInterface
public interface ShapeInsetsFunction
extends ThrowingFunction4<java.lang.Integer,​java.lang.Integer,​java.lang.Integer,​java.lang.Integer,​java.awt.Insets,​NoException>
It's a ThrowingFunction4 that throws NoException (just a way to avoid throwing stuff), takes in 4 integers (which should be x, y, width, and height), and returns an Insets. This interface exists solely as shorthand for using the long ThrowingFunction4 name.
